Dipteryx odorata

   [5505.jpg]
   Authority (Aublet) Willd.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Coumarouna odorata Aubl., Coumarouna micrantha (Harms) Ducke
   Common names tonka bean, Dutch tonka bean, coumara nut, fava-tonca,
   feijao baru, feijao coco, cumaru verdadeiro, sarrapia'
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 5505

   Notes
   SOURCES (D. odorata (Aubl.) Willd.)
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 258-263 [RAIN, FER, DRA]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 384 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 15 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1981 pp 79-81 [LIG, DRA, FER, TEXT, RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial tree. 2 years to first harvest if carefully cultivated, and
   7-10 years to first harvest without cultivation. The tree flowers in
   March-May and fruit in June-July. Fresh pods are harvested in June-July
   and fallen pods in January-March.
   COMMON NAMES
   Tonka bean, Cimaru, Tonga, Cumaru, Tonquin.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: Coumarouna odora, C. punctata. Tonka bean is
   native of South America, being most abundant along the tributaries of
   the Orinoco river in Venezuela. It can reach a height of 25-30 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
